<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 08 at 12:13PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Bedford and southwestern Botetourt Counties through 1245 PM EDT...
At 1212 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fincastle, or near Troutville, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Buchanan...
Troutville...
Montvale...
Fincastle...
Nace...
Daleville...
and Springwood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
